[0.0, "o", "\u001b[92m$\u001b[0m exhibit selfcheck\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "## \u2705 Reproduced. Failing test attached.\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "**Report as understood:** split_bill drops remainder cents; splits don't sum to total\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "**Symptom:** `wrong_value`\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "The test below **fails on the current code** and did so on 2/2 runs. It should pass once the bug is fixed; it asserts the *expected* behavior.\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "```python\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "from buggy_calc import split_bill\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "def test_split_bill_conserves_total():\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "    total = 100\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "    splits = split_bill(total, 3)\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "    assert sum(splits) == total, f\"expected splits to sum to {total}, got {sum(splits)}\"\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "```\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "### Gates\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "| gate | result | detail |\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "|---|---|---|\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "| collects | pass | pytest collected the file |\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "| fails_on_head | pass | assertion: AssertionError AssertionError: expected splits to sum to 100, got 99 assert 99 == 100  +  where 99 = sum([33, 33, 33]) |\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "| symptom_match | pass | wrong-value report requires an assertion failure, observed assertion |\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "| stable | pass | failed identically on 2/2 runs |\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "| known_good (advisory) | pass | no known-good ref reported; skipped |\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "### Observed failure\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "```text\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "AssertionError: AssertionError: expected splits to sum to 100, got 99\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "assert 99 == 100\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", " +  where 99 = sum([33, 33, 33])\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "```\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "<sub>exhibit-a v0.1.0. verdicts are computed by a deterministic gate engine; the LLM only drafts tests, it never grades them. [how it works](https://github.com/Dhxnx-git/exhibit-a#how-it-works)</sub>\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "============================================================\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "selfcheck verdict: CONFIRMED\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "selfcheck: PASS \u2705\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "\u001b[92m$\u001b[0m exhibit run --repo examples/buggy_calc \\\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "      --plan-file examples/sample_plan.json \\\r\n"]
[15.007, "o", "      --candidates-file examples/sample_candidates.json\r\n"]
